0.4:
	* Fix the bug that other overlays of other add-ons do not work

0.4:
	* Support recipients (To and Cc) in addition to senders
	* Support up to Thunderbird 3.2a1pre
	* Change the default behavior to replace the contents of default columns instead of creating new columns
	* Fix several bugs about displaying
	
0.3:
	* Add options to select attributes and labels to be displayed, and to specify format strings
	* Add support of displaying any address book attributes
	* Add support of displaying columns in the search dialog and search folders
	* Add a namespace scheme to avoid conflict with other extensions
	* Change the default column label for the "Display Name" attribute to "Sender Name"
	* Fix the bug that column positions are not saved
	* Fix the bug double-quoting the display name when it contains commas
